JOHANNESBURG - The local banking sector has lost billions since last week's Cabinet reshuffle.The sector says it s financially sound and prepared to deal with the impact of credit rating downgrades. Nedbank and Standard Bank have assured investors they are ready to manage the volatility and pressure ahead.South African banks now face declining returns and rising bad debt as lenders are expected to charge more for their loans.READ: Rand slumps nearly 3% on downgradeThis after ratings agency Standard and Poor s cut the country s sovereign credit rating to junk.The JSE s banking index tumbled to its lowest level in six months after yesterday's downgrade.Meanwhile, the rand s extending its losing streak into a seventh straight session on Tuesday.The local currency has fallen almost two percent on Tuesday morning following the ratings downgrade.It threatens to push inflation higher in the country, following months of improvements.eNCA